Description:
 Jannik Sinner and Jiri Lehecka will face off Sunday in the final at the Miami Open presented by Itau, where a milestone moment is on the line for both players. 

 The No. 2 player in the PIF ATP Rankings, Sinner is on the brink of becoming the first man to complete the coveted ‘Sunshine Double' of winning Indian Wells and Miami in the same year since Roger Federer in 2017. Standing in the Italian's way at Hard Rock Stadium is 21st seed Lehecka, who is aiming to win his maiden ATP Masters 1000 trophy. Find out when the final is below. 

 The final between Sinner and Lehecka will begin not before 3 p.m. local time (EDT) / 8 p.m. CET on Sunday. 

Sinner leads Lehecka 3-0 in their Lexus ATP Head2Head series. The Italian did not drop a set across his three victories, which came in Indian Wells and Beijing in 2024 and at 2025 Roland Garros, respectively. 



















































































